cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.NE 

This paper deals with domain adaptation for image classification tasks, which is a common problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the use of discriminative features and geometric structure, which suggests that it may also be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper proposes new models for domain adaptation, which could also be relevant to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
